<p itemprop="description">People management involves leading, developing, and supporting individuals and teams to achieve their potential while delivering organizational objectives and maintaining high performance standards.</p>

<div class="proficiency-levels">
    <h2>Proficiency Levels</h2>

    <ol class="skill-levels">
        <li>
            <h3>Awareness</h3>
            <p>You can understand the principles of people management and recognise the importance of effective leadership and team development in government contexts.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Working</h3>
            <p>You can manage small teams effectively, conduct performance conversations, support professional development, and handle basic HR processes and procedures.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Practitioner</h3>
            <p>You can manage larger teams and departments, develop talent pipelines, handle complex people issues, and create high-performing team cultures.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Expert</h3>
            <p>You can lead organizational people strategy, drive cultural change, establish people management frameworks, and influence HR policy across government.</p>
        </li>
    </ol>
</div>

